<!--
    PUF France Use Case 4: Invoice Partially Paid by Third Party Known at Invoicing
    (Facture à payer par l'acheteur et prise en charge partiellement par un tiers connu à la facturation)
    
    Business Scenario:
    - Car repair invoice with insurance coverage
    - Third-party PAYER (insurer) pays part of the invoice to SELLER
    - BUYER pays remainder (deductible + ALL VAT)
    - Classic insurance scenario with deductible franchise
    
    Key Requirements:
    - Business process B1: Standard invoice
    - BT-113 (Prepaid amount): Amount to be paid by third-party PAYER (insurer portion)
    - BT-115 (Amount due): BT-112 - BT-113 (BUYER pays deductible + VAT)
    - Third-party PAYER: EXT-FR-FE-BG-02 (recommended for UC4)
    
    Financial Breakdown Example:
    - Repair services: 3000.00 EUR (net)
    - VAT 20%: 600.00 EUR
    - Total with VAT: 3600.00 EUR
    - Insurance deductible: 500.00 EUR
    - Insurer pays: 2500.00 EUR (3000 - 500 deductible, NO VAT)
    - BUYER pays: 1100.00 EUR (500 deductible + 600 VAT)
    
    Critical VAT Rule:
    - Insurer ONLY pays non-VAT amount (minus deductible)
    - BUYER must pay ALL VAT + deductible
    - Prevents double VAT benefit for deductible companies
    
    French Text Codes (BT-21/BT-22):
    - #REG#: Company legal form and share capital
    - #ABL#: Trade register number (RCS)
    - #AAI#: APE business activity code
    - #PMD#: Late payment penalties
    - #PMT#: Fixed collection costs indemnity (€40)
    - #BAR#: Treatment type (B2B e-invoicing)
    - #PAI#: MANDATORY - Third party payment information (partial payment by insurer)
-->
